    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i'll try to stick to the impact-based phrasing. it's just tricky because sometimes the behavior feels less like a \"skill gap\" and more like just a really annoying personality thing. like, they just seem to thrive on a bit of chaos or being difficult for the sake of it. do you have any advice for when an employee's \"vibe\" is just fundamentally disruptive to the office culture even if their technical output is okay?",
