      "content": "When the issue is truly a personality mismatch affecting culture, you must pivot the discussion from \"skills\" to \"professional conduct\" or \"team contribution.\" You can state that their current interactions occasionally create an environment that hinders team cohesion or momentum. Frame it as needing to align their professional presence with the team's established values and working style. This sets a boundary around cultural expectations, which is a management responsibility.",
      "source": "target",
